SIMPLE: thyself
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thyself
<hw>Thy*self"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>pron.</pos> <def>An emphasized
form of the personal pronoun of the second person; -- used as a subject
commonly with <xex>thou</xex>; <as>as, thou <ex>thyself</ex> shalt
go</as>; that is, thou shalt go, and no other. It is sometimes used,
especially in the predicate, without <xex>thou</xex>, and in the
nominative as well as in the objective case.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Thyself</qex> shalt see the act.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ere I do thee, thou to <qex>thyself</qex> wast cruel.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tiar</ent>⟦br⟧
